\subtree{
\title{Implementing Anti-Phishing Training Program}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Security awareness training is the human layer of phishing defense. An effective anti-phishing training program combines regular simulations, interactive learning modules, metric tracking, and positive reinforcement to build a security-conscious culture. This skill covers designing, deploying, and measuring a comprehensive phishing awareness program using platforms like KnowBe4, Proofpoint Security Awareness, and open-source alternatives.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{When deploying or configuring implementing anti phishing training program capabilities in your environment}
\li{When establishing security controls aligned to compliance requirements}
\li{When building or improving security architecture for this domain}
\li{When conducting security assessments that require this implementation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Prerequisites}
\ul{
\li{Management buy-in and budget approval}
\li{Security awareness training platform (KnowBe4, Proofpoint SAT, Cofense)}
\li{Employee email list and organizational structure}
\li{Baseline phishing susceptibility data (from initial simulation)}
\li{Learning management system (LMS) integration capability}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Training Program Pillars}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Baseline Assessment}: Initial phishing simulation to measure current susceptibility}
\li{\strong{Interactive Training}: Role-based modules covering phishing identification}
\li{\strong{Regular Simulations}: Monthly/quarterly phishing tests with progressive difficulty}
\li{\strong{Just-in-Time Learning}: Immediate training after a user fails a simulation}
\li{\strong{Positive Reinforcement}: Recognition for reporting phishing correctly}
\li{\strong{Metrics & Reporting}: Track improvement over time by department and role}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{SANS Security Awareness Maturity Model}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Level 1}: Non-existent - No program}
\li{\strong{Level 2}: Compliance-focused - Annual checkbox training}
\li{\strong{Level 3}: Promoting Awareness - Engaging, regular content}
\li{\strong{Level 4}: Long-term Sustainment - Continuous program with culture change}
\li{\strong{Level 5}: Metrics Framework - Risk-based measurement and optimization}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Establish Baseline}
\ul{
\li{Run initial phishing simulation across all departments}
\li{Measure click rate, submit rate, and report rate}
\li{Identify high-risk departments and roles}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Design Curriculum}
\ul{
\li{\strong{General awareness}: Phishing identification basics for all employees}
\li{\strong{Role-specific}: Finance (BEC/wire fraud), IT (credential phishing), Executives (whaling)}
\li{\strong{Progressive difficulty}: Beginner, intermediate, advanced modules}
\li{\strong{Micro-learning}: Short (3-5 minute) frequent sessions vs. annual marathon}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Deploy Training Platform}
\ul{
\li{Configure KnowBe4/Proofpoint SAT with organizational groups}
\li{Set up automated enrollment workflows}
\li{Integrate with LMS for completion tracking}
\li{Configure reporting dashboards}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 4: Run Continuous Simulations}
\ul{
\li{Monthly simulations with varied scenarios}
\li{Increase difficulty based on organizational performance}
\li{Include diverse attack types: links, attachments, QR codes, BEC}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 5: Measure and Optimize}
\p{Use \code{\startverb scripts/process.py\stopverb} to analyze training completion, simulation results, and program effectiveness over time.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tools & Resources}
\ul{
\li{\strong{KnowBe4}: https://www.knowbe4.com/}
\li{\strong{Proofpoint Security Awareness}: https://www.proofpoint.com/us/products/security-awareness-training}
\li{\strong{Cofense PhishMe}: https://cofense.com/}
\li{\strong{SANS Security Awareness}: https://www.sans.org/security-awareness-training/}
\li{\strong{Terranova Security}: https://terranovasecurity.com/}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Validation}
\ul{
\li{90\%+ training completion rate across organization}
\li{Measurable reduction in phishing click rate over 6 months}
\li{Increase in user phishing report rate}
\li{Department-level improvement tracking}
}
}
}